{"tid":504553,"cid":5,"subCid":0,"title":"最老化石證35億年前有生命","createTime":"2017-12-20T06:46:37.000Z","updateTime":"2017-12-20T07:06:41.000Z","uid":33072,"like":6,"dislike":0,"uniUserReply":2,"replies":[{"pid":"1db04330eab053d56f218affc1268d69d4f4acff","tid":504553,"uid":33072,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2017-12-20T06:46:37.000Z","msg":"<img src=\"https://fs.mingpao.com/ins/20171219/s00005/46d095ab93a83d552336797b5ab268ea.jpg\" data-thumbnail-src=\"https://i.lih.kg/thumbnail?u=https%3A%2F%2Ffs.mingpao.com%2Fins%2F20171219%2Fs00005%2F46d095ab93a83d552336797b5ab268ea.jpg&h=2094700d&s={SIZE}\" /><br />\n<br />\n美國一項微生物化石研究結果顯示，從澳洲發現的最古老化石得出直接證據，確認35億年前已有細菌等微生物存活。<br />\n<br />\n科學家利用二次離子質譜法（SIMS），在11塊澳洲出土的微生物化石板中，鑑別出5種細菌。參與研究的加州大學古生物學家邵夫（William Schopf）及威斯康星大學地質學家維利（John Valley）表示，研究顯示地球出現生命的時間可追溯至35億年前，甚至40億年前，當時地球仍未有氧氣，但那時的生物已經多種多樣。<br />\n<br />\n邵夫稱，「生命一定是很早就出現了，但是還沒有人知道究竟有多早。」他認為研究意義重大，35億年前的地球出現生命，說明宇宙出現生命的時間可能更早。<br />\n<br />\n華盛頓大學化學家蓋博（Lara Gamble）認為，研究是經過精心設計，可以確保測量準確。<br />\n<br />\n醬油：<a href=\"https://news.mingpao.com/ins/instantnews/web_tc/article/20171219/s00005/1513660713763\" data-sr-url=\"https://r.lihkg.com/link?u=https%3A%2F%2Fnews.mingpao.com%2Fins%2Finstantnews%2Fweb_tc%2Farticle%2F20171219%2Fs00005%2F1513660713763&d=Xg0MilhLFswsUtwzR4mAVCwN645TRhVPBLeqKBQ2Igw%3D&h=8bbc8524\" data-ef-url=\"https://embed.lih.kg/frame?u=https%3A%2F%2Fnews.mingpao.com%2Fins%2Finstantnews%2Fweb_tc%2Farticle%2F20171219%2Fs00005%2F1513660713763&h=36675b56\" target=\"_blank\">https://news.mingpao.com/ins/instantnews/web_tc/article/20171219/s00005/1513660713763</a>"},{"pid":"ca72d722ed3cc51830d2285d49a629b192b285c2","tid":504553,"uid":42767,"like":3,"dislike":0,"score":3,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2017-12-20T07:06:41.000Z","msg":"耶撚: 地球得6000年"}]}